reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: Moving Zimbabwe Towards Malaria Elimination: strengthening evidence based programming

description.narrative: Zimbabwe - Malaria - The Ministry of Health and Child Care of the Republic of Zimbabwe - MOHCC. This program has the following goals: To reduce malaria incidence to 5/1000 and malaria deaths by at least 90% of the 2015 figure by 2020. The objectives of this program are: To protect at least 85% of the population at risk of malaria with an appropriate malaria prevention interventions for the period 2016-2020.. To provide prompt and appropriate treatment to all confirmed malaria cases by 2018 and maintain up to 2020. To strengthen surveillance, monitoring and evaluation for all malaria interventions for the period 2016-2020. To eliminate local malaria transmission in at least 9 districts by 2020. To increase utilization of all malaria interventions to at least 85% by 2020. To provide effective leadership and an enabling environment for optimal program management and coordination at all levels by 2020
